<h2 id="strumming-pattern">Strumming pattern</h2>

<p>First, understand that we want to accept the 2 and the 4 counts. If we look at two measures (8 beats total), this would look like this:</p>

<div class="language-plaintext highlighter-rouge"><div class="highlight"><pre class="highlight"><code>1 + 2 + 3 + 4 + 1 + 2 + 3 + 4 +
    D       D       D       D
</code></pre></div></div>

<p>From there, weâ€™ll want to mute (silence) all of the strings on the 3 count. Do this while keeping the accent on the 2 and 4 beats.</p>

<div class="language-plaintext highlighter-rouge"><div class="highlight"><pre class="highlight"><code>1 + 2 + 3 + 4 + 1 + 2 + 3 + 4 +
    D   x   D       D   x   D
</code></pre></div></div>

<p>Next, add an up strum on the â€œ2 +â€ count of each measure.</p>

<div class="language-plaintext highlighter-rouge"><div class="highlight"><pre class="highlight"><code>1 + 2 + 3 + 4 + 1 + 2 + 3 + 4 +
    D U x   D       D U x   D
</code></pre></div></div>

<p>And from there, add an up strum to the â€œ1 +â€ count.</p>

<div class="language-plaintext highlighter-rouge"><div class="highlight"><pre class="highlight"><code>1 + 2 + 3 + 4 + 1 + 2 + 3 + 4 +
  U D U x   D     U D U x   D
</code></pre></div></div>

<p>Then, practice removing the â€œ2â€ count down strum.</p>

<div class="language-plaintext highlighter-rouge"><div class="highlight"><pre class="highlight"><code>1 + 2 + 3 + 4 + 1 + 2 + 3 + 4 +
  U   U x   D     U   U x   D
</code></pre></div></div>

<p>Finally, try mixing and matching all of the above! For example, youâ€™ll hear this on the album quite a bit:</p>

<div class="language-plaintext highlighter-rouge"><div class="highlight"><pre class="highlight"><code>1 + 2 + 3 + 4 + 1 + 2 + 3 + 4 +
  U   U x   D     U D U x   D
</code></pre></div></div>

